{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, GPT, a generative text model, required a specific system prompt besides the document text to guide a zero-shot translation process: \"Translate the document to Dutch (Nederlands).",
    "Keep the formatting the same, including the in-text annotations: [[span][code]].",
    "\"This approach allowed us to compare a traditional translation service with a state-of-the-art generative text model in preserving annotated concept locations during translation.",
    "To evaluate the quality of annotation preservation, we compared descriptive statistics like document size and the number of annotations before and after translation.",
    "Additionally, we quantified formatting errors, i.e., the erroneous placing of brackets in the translated text, by counting the CUIs in the final translated text, as an annotation with a wrong bracket pattern is not extracted, and its CUI remains in the text."
  ]
}